Referring to Brexit, the commentator said on Twitter: “When the UK had the worst recession in the G7, you blamed Covid. Now the UK has the worst inflation in the G7, you're blaming Russia.” “At some point, you've gotta ask yourself why our economy seems to be more vulnerable to these 'global problems'. What did we do?“ But one eagle eyed Twitter user, @tartantory, pointed out that the UK has the highest GDP in the G7. They said: “We've had the highest increase in GDP in the G7 due to Brexit.” For 2021 as a whole, UK GDP growth was 7.4 percent and the highest in the G7, according to the Commons Library. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...